-- Colombia Raises Nation’s Minimum Wage by 5.8%, Portafolio Says
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2011-12-15T20:38:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/colombia-raises-nation-s-minimum-wage-by-5-8-portafolio-says.html
Colombia ’s government reached an
agreement with workers and business leaders to raise the monthly
minimum wage by 5.8 percent starting in January, Portafolio
newspaper  said  without saying where it obtained the information.  The monthly wage was raised to 566,700 pesos ($293), the
Bogota-based daily said. The central bank targets inflation
between 2 percent and 4 percent this year and next.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Jaramillo in Bogota at 
 ajaramillo1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
